        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 10:48PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1048 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mertzon, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mertzon, Sherwood, and Us-67 Near The Irion-Tom Green County Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
